    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for expat.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "Expat is a C library for parsing XML documents.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* expat: stack exhaustion in doctype parsing (CVE-2022-25313)\n\n* expat: integer overflow in copyString() (CVE-2022-25314)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
